    "last_edit_date" : 1727349979,
    "creation_date" : 1727349941,
    "answer_id" : 79027052,
    "question_id" : 2447867,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I am using Manjaro Sway Linux based on Arch, and for me, the <code>netbeans.conf</code> file was located in <code>usr/etc/netbeans.conf</code>. I was also having the problem to locate the file, and thus performed a search operation in the root directory using terminal which helped.\n<code>sudo find / -type f -name &quot;netbeans.conf&quot;</code>.</p>\n"
