  "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/2447867/where-is-the-netbeans-config-file-netbeans-conf-located",
  "title" : "where is the NetBeans config file (netbeans.conf) located?",
  "body" : "<p>my NetBeans has ugly fonts in interface. I'm going to make antialiasing for it. In internet I saw that there is should be</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>-J-Dswing.aatext=true -J-Dawt.useSystemAAFontSettings=on</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>in <strong>netbeans_default_options</strong>. This file should be located in /etc/netbeans.conf. But there isn't this file. I have NetBeans 6.8. Help, please.</p>\n<p><strong>UPD</strong>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[ockonal@wincode ~]$ cd ~/.netbeans/6.8/</p>\n<p>[ockonal@wincode 6.8]$ ls</p>\n<p>ant  build.properties  docs     lib   modules  sources\nupdate_tracking bin  config<br />\njsstubs  lock  native   update   var</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><strong>UPD2</strong>\nWith utilite find I did:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>find / -name 'netbeans.conf'</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This gave me:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>/usr/share/netbeans/etc/netbeans.conf</p>\n</blockquote>\n"
